Short version: I’d give this place a sky full of stars not just 5. The food is mouthwatering. The people are warm and will remind you of home. AND SO CLEAN!!!!!  Long version: The person (I feel terrible for not not asking for his name) who took our take-out order first offered us a glass of water because he knew we had been driving for long before that. He had our order ready. He was wearing a mask the right way and when we were paying, he sanitised our card, swiped, sanitised again and returned it. He sanitised the pen that we had to sign with. When one of my friends said she’d go to the car, he said it may not be safe and walked her out to the car. He enquired about our families and gave us dessert to go. He was so warm that he literally reminded us of home. Now the food - we got home and ate our food only to feel instant regret that we didn’t order enough to over eat. Not joking.  It was SO good and the way they had packed the whole thing was something else!  Overall, I recommend this place 10/10. When in Atlanta, be sure to go to Aamar’s!

Recently visited this Amazing place (Aamar Indian cuisine ) @Downtown Atlanta this one is the good places in Atlanta who serves some good Indian delicious food i been here very recently this is small restaurant but they  have good quantity and quality food the ambience was average not that pleasing but when i come towards the food they do great quality of food now talking about food when u order some curry dishes they personally come to you and ask how u wanna do it if u wanna make it spicy ,medium ,or little sweet this was a good gesture by them and after food when it comes to dessert i ordered some phirni and laal mohan ie gulab jamun they were very delicious Here are  food i ordered 1.chef special chicken tikka masala 2.Naan 3.Rice 4.laal mohan -(gulab jamun) 5.phirni Ratings:- Food-4/5 Ambience-3/5 Service-4/5 Overall-4/5 I will definitely recommend this restaurant to someone who is reading my review go and check them out 🤩🤩

We've had take out from here as well as gone to the restaurant itself.  Let's just start off by saying the food is absolutely fantastic as far as flavor is concerned. I've definitely had my fair share of chicken tikka masalas and the sauce in this one is smooth and creamy and just right. Additionally, the samosas come fresh out of the kitchen when you're dining here and the pastry shell as well as the insides are just right. My wife also introduced me to pikora and that was a new and delicious experience. The only thing I would consider to be a con is the portion size. For the amount that you're paying for the dishes, the portions could probably be just a tad larger and in that respect I'd probably give a 4.75.  As far as the restaurant itself is concerned, it is definitely a hole in the wall type place nestled right next to the bottom floor of a parking garage. Perhaps 6 tables in total, 3 tables for 4 and 3 tables for 2. The food is served with disposable everything, likely because there is minimal room to perform dish washing duties. For this aesthetic reason, I'd probably give it 4.5 stars if that was a possibility.
